en_172333_0	The Joint Opposition will file seven petitions in the Supreme Court today and tomorrow against the Provincial Council Elections Amendment Act.
en_172333_1	Former Chief Justice Sarath N. Silva has already filed a Fundamental Rights petition against the Act, before the Supreme Court.
en_172333_2	In his petition, he requests the Supreme Court to issue an order to the Election Commission to hold the election according to the old method.
